title: Castro, Obama, Pope Francis--Oh My!
text:
Castro, Obama, Pope Francis--Oh My! September 18, 2015 
Almost half of Manhattan will be off limits to the public when Pope Francis gets to New York next Friday—and he’s just one of the many famous tourists expected to gridlock the Big Apple next week. Besides the Pope’s visit, which is scheduled for Sept. 25, Raul Castro, in his first-ever U.S. appearance, and President Obama will both address the United Nations on Monday, Sept. 28. Other diplomats from around the world are expected to attend the U.N.’s General Assembly meeting, leaving a conclave of state vehicles with diplomatic plates to further clog the city streets. New Jersey Transit and the Long Island Railroad also are expecting overcrowding.
